Day 6: Bug Reporting & Defect Management with ChatGPT
What is a Bug?
A Bug (Defect) is a flaw in the software where the actual behavior differs from the expected behavior.
Example
Requirement:
User should be able to log in using valid email and password.
Actual:
Login fails even with valid credentials.
This is a bug.
__________________________________________________
 2: Defect vs Error vs Failure  
Term	        Meaning                            	Example
Error        	Human mistake	                    Developer writes incorrect logic
Defect (Bug)	Issue in software	                Login button not working
Failure      	Software fails during execution	    Application crashes after clicking Login
__________________________________________________
3.Bug Life Cycle
The bug life cycle describes the journey of a bug from discovery to closure.
New
 ↓
Assigned
 ↓
Open
 ↓
In Progress
 ↓
Fixed
 ↓
Retest
 ↓
Closed

Possible alternate paths:
Rejected
Duplicate
Cannot Reproduce
Deferred
Not a Bug
Reopened

_____________________________________________________________________________
Common Statuses
Status	        Meaning
New	          QA reported the bug
Assigned	    Assigned to developer
Open	        Developer accepted it
Fixed	        Code updated
Retest	      QA verifies the fix
Closed	      Fix confirmed
Reopened	    Still failing
Deferred	    Fix postponed
Duplicate	    Already reported
Rejected	    Not considered a valid defect
